node.text: “The last time I wore my underwear over my pants I felt like a hero,” reveals #PriyankaChopraJonas, the September cover star of @VogueIndia. Watch as the actor, singer, @Bulgari ambassador and philanthropist explains why exactly she’d like to roll around on Mars, debates riding an elephant or a giraffe to go to work, and sings the theme tune to her life.

node.title: @PriyankaChopra Jonas takes on Vogue’s Impossible Questions

node.text:
Don’t miss the exhibition dedicated to the work of #IrvingPenn in collaboration with #VogueItalia and the Irving Penn Foundation, on display at @CardiGallery in Milano, from today to December 22nd. 

Considered to be one of the greatest photographers of the 20th century, Irving Penn (1917-2009) radically modernized photography as a medium, creating a canon that would manifest a rich and influential legacy of commercial and personal work. Penn joined @VogueMagazine in the early 1940s and he continued to work with the magazine throughout his career. Breaking all convention, Penn approached photography as an artist, opening his own studio and expanding the medium’s creative potential at a time when the photograph was primarily understood as a means of communication.

Click the link in bio if you want to discover more about the exhibition.
Text by Vogue Italia’s Culture Editor @_Federico_Chiara_

Take a look at the video to discover how the project was born.

Credits
Talent Costanza Starrabba wearing @off____white 
Video by @maranif

node.text: "This tattoo got me into a lot of trouble because I had a contract and I wasn't supposed to get tattoos and I did; but it was worth it because I love this tattoo and the meaning behind it". node.title: @JourdanDunn reveals the empowering message of her tattoos

node.text:
Today we announce the 35 photographers selected for the upcoming #PhotoVogueFestival exhibition through the open call on #PhotoVogue, @Picter_com and Instagram. On Picter alone we received 24.913 images, 2.949 projects by 2.513 photographers from 98 different countries, 6 continents. 
 
Here are the selected artists: @tendercoconut_, @Alessandro.Iovino_, @BettinaPittaluga, @BryanThomasphoto, @delaliayivi, @diiegotv, @di_mathopa, @ElenaHelfrecht, @Elliott.Verdier, @FabioLasin, @Gabriele.Cecconi, @heathatrottlives, @Reanie_Beanie, @l4artiste, @jaircoll, @JodiemBateman, @Juan_Brenner, @Kaiykym, @LauraPannack, @lebo.th, @LeonardPongo, @LisandroSuriel, @Kuca_Magda, @MousLamrabat, @plantationofficial, @elriveriver, @RobertAndyCoombs2, @tondopo, @SaraBennettBrooklyn, @SilvanaTrevale, @SuleikaMueller, @Sushavan_Nandy, @africatotheworldzw, @thembinkosih15, @panremembrance. The artists have been selected by an international jury consisting of experts from across the world, with different backgrounds and vision so as to try to provide the most inclusive and multifaceted perspective. 
 
Photo Vogue Festival has always tried to challenge the danger of single, monolithic stories, and to push a multiplicity of points of view. For its 6th edition, titled “Reframing History”, we wanted to explore the projects that have reclaimed an alternative, different way of telling a tale. 
For the very first time - as part of the Reframing History scouting initiative - PVF launched a grant in collaboration with Studio RM, a prestigious creative studio with offices in London and New York, specialising in colour grading and post production for film, print and digital.
The two participants that will receive a 5,000€ cash grant each, are Lisandro Suriel and River Claure. 
 
Discover more about #VIReframingHistory at the link in bio.

node.text: “I basically spent 2020 indoors and, when I was bored in the middle of quarantine, for the first time ever I started playing with makeup,” says Eiza González. Watch the Mexican actor and star of Godzilla Vs Kong reveal her go-to makeup tricks for statement eyes. Directed by @rjgoni.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue Italia on September 11, 2021 tagging @brandonmaxwell. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text: @BrandonMaxwell was busier than usual backstage because he was wearing two hats: designer and stylist. “I wanted to do something that felt authentic,” he said. “When I started I was maybe insecure about not having a fashion education, so I felt I needed to be more serious. But I’m not that serious a person. During the pandemic, I decided that if I got the opportunity ever again, I’d like to do it as me.” Click the link in bio to read the full review by @VogueRunway’s @NicolePhelps. Photographed by @HunterAbrams.

node.text:
Digital Portfolio Revie​​w: @MaggieSteber is one of the portfolio reviewers of the sixth edition of #PhotoVogueFestival 2021.
 
For your chance to be shortlisted, send by October 15th an email to pvf@condenast.it accompanied by your portfolio (a selection of 10/15 images in pdf format), a biography, a contact number and a link to your website. The free digital portfolio review is open to any kind of photographic genre, from art and fashion to photojournalism and documentary. If selected you won't need to be in Milan like for the past editions because the portfolio review is digital. You can apply from anywhere!
 
Discover more via link in bio.

node.text: “In a time of temporary crisis we’ve created a timeless project on intimacy and love through photographing couples at their homes,” say @Ronabarphotos & @ofekavshalom (@fotometro.art), the artists behind these images. “The photographs allow a unique and honest glimpse into the world that the couples created themselves. The heart of the project lays in the authentic and diverse forms of real-life relationships.” Click the link in bio to see more pictures.

node.text: @the.PeterDo gave a hand-written note to each and every one of his guests. In the letter, he likened designing his new collection—the first he’s showing on the runway—to making Pho with his dad as a teen. Do father and son were Vietnamese immigrants in Philadelphia, and cooking the traditional soup was a weekend bonding exercise. “A good Pho is reduced and edited, to an essence” he wrote. “It is comforting and it feels like home… Welcome to our home.” Click the link in bio to read the full review by @VogueRunway’s @NicolePhelps. Photographed by @HunterAbrams.

node.text: “Senza Fine” is the latest documentary film dedicated to Italian icon @OrnellaVanoniofficialpage, a legendary singer, forever shrouded in a halo of myth. Presented at #VeniceFilmFestival’s Giornate degli Autori, the documentary is the result of the encounter between #OrnellaVanoni and director @ElisaFuksas: tap the link in bio to discover more. Text by @VittoriaGabardi.

node.text: @UllaJohnson is the first designer to have secured the Brooklyn Botanic Garden for a show. It’s an idyllic spot no matter the conditions, but the weather gods were more agreeable than usual this morning. There wasn’t a cloud in the sky and the temperature was mild. Below the Attacca Quartet, cicadas were making music of their own. The day’s packed schedule would require two more commutes back and forth to Brooklyn, but this was a moment of calm. “The garden was a bit of an oasis for me during this last chapter,” said Johnson, who lives nearby. “We’ve all been doing a lot of reflection, and in those moments I decided I wanted to tell a story about pauses.” Click the link in bio to read the full review by @VogueRunway’s @NicolePhelps. Photographed by @HunterAbrams.

node.text:
@Tess_McMillan brings Vogue behind-the-scenes at the @COACH Spring-Summer 2022 Show by @StuartVevers presented at #NewYorkFashionWeek. Watch the full takeover in #VogueItalia’s Instagram Stories and tap the link in bio to see every single look. 
Special thanks to @ImgModels.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Vogue Italia in Manhattan, New York. May be an image of skyscraper.

node.text:
"What does 20 years feel like? An eon, if we’re being honest. The world has changed so dramatically since that September morning. But in other ways, the tragedy of that day and its weight of history never disappears. If you lost a loved one, you carry the heaviest memories. And if you live in New York, you have your own 9/11."
 
At the link in our bio, Anna Wintour shares a personal essay on the strength and beauty of New York City, and why we will #NeverForget 9/11, twenty years on. Photographed by @AnnieLeibovitz, Vogue, September 2021

node.text: #JenniferLopez and #BenAffleck made their appearance on the #VeniceFilmFestival red carpet tonight for the premiere of #TheLastDuel — where Affleck stars along with #JodieCorner and #MattDamon. Click the link in bio to discover more.

node.text: If you’re in town for #MilanDesignWeek, the #BarBasso is definitely the place to be for a good Italian aperitivo—and for showing off your personality and meeting the right people too. At link in bio, photographer @PavelGolik shared with #VogueItalia a visual diary of what to expect from this iconic milanese spot.
